# agenticDiagram — optional configuration.
#
# Every variable here is OPTIONAL; the app runs fine with none set. They are
# inherited from the upstream mermaid-live-editor and mostly tune analytics,
# external renderers, and privacy/legal links. To use them, copy this file to
# `.env` (which is gitignored) and uncomment what you need.
#
# Notes:
#   - Client-exposed vars MUST keep the `MERMAID_` prefix — Vite only forwards
#     that prefix to browser code (see `envPrefix` in vite.config.js).
#   - `MERMAID_BASE_PATH` is read at build time by svelte.config.js; the rest
#     are read via import.meta.env in src/lib/util/env.ts.
#   - The Gemini AI feature does NOT read a key from here. You enter your
#     Google Gemini API key in the app's UI and it is stored client-side
#     (localStorage), never in the repo or the build.

# --- Deployment ---
# Serve the app under a sub-path instead of the domain root, e.g. "/diagrams".
# Default: "" (served at root).
# MERMAID_BASE_PATH=

# --- External renderers (advanced; leave unset to render in-browser) ---
# URL of a self-hosted mermaid render service.
# Default: "" (render locally in the browser).
# MERMAID_RENDERER_URL=
# URL of a Kroki renderer for non-mermaid diagram types.
# Default: "".
# MERMAID_KROKI_RENDERER_URL=

# --- Analytics (Plausible; disabled unless both are set) ---
# Plausible endpoint URL. Default: "" (analytics off).
# MERMAID_ANALYTICS_URL=
# Domain to report to Plausible. Default: "".
# MERMAID_DOMAIN=

# --- Links & UI ---
# Base URL for "docs" links in the UI. Default: "https://mermaid.js.org".
# MERMAID_DOCS_URL=
# Show "Open in Mermaid Chart" links. Set to "true" to enable. Default: false.
# MERMAID_IS_ENABLED_MERMAID_CHART_LINKS=

# --- Privacy / legal ---
# URL of your privacy policy, shown in the privacy notice. Default: "".
# MERMAID_PRIVACY_POLICY_URL=
# Hide the privacy policy notice entirely. Set to "true" to hide. Default: false.
# MERMAID_HIDE_PRIVACY_POLICY=
